    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I migrate from 10Web to Framer?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">No direct migration. You'd export WordPress content from 10Web, rebuild in Framer. Both support content import via CSV, but the structure differs. Migration is possible but requires manual work. Plan ahead.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Which loads faster?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Framer. My tests: Framer ~0.8s, 10Web ~2.4s. WordPress overhead is real. Both pass Core Web Vitals, but Framer's performance is exceptional. If speed is critical, Framer wins.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Do both support custom domains?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Yes. Both connect custom domains on paid plans. No meaningful difference here. 10Web: connect via dashboard. Framer: connect via settings. Both work reliably.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Which has better SEO?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Framer loads faster (better Core Web Vitals). 10Web has WordPress SEO plugins (Yoast, RankMath). In practice: both can rank. Framer has technical edge. 10Web wins if you configure plugins properly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I hire developers for either?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">10Web: Any WordPress developer (millions worldwide). Framer: Growing ecosystem, but fewer specialists. If you want to hand off work later, 10Web has more available talent. For Framer, you'll need to find specialists or learn it yourself.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Which is better for blogging?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">10Web. WordPress is built for blogging. Categories, tags, RSS, comments, schedulingâ€”everything. Framer has basic CMS but lacks advanced blogging features. For serious content marketing, 10Web wins.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I use my existing WordPress theme?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">With 10Web: yes, import any WordPress theme. With Framer: no, you'd rebuild from scratch. If you have existing WordPress sites you want to enhance, 10Web is the clear path. Framer is a fresh start.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

